British Chancellor of theExchequer Nigel Lawson pledged to continue making defeat ofinflation a top priority.    Speaking to the ruling Central Council of the ConservativeParty, Lawson said "We will continue to make defeat of inflationa top priority until it is eliminated altogether."    Year on year inflation is running at 3.7 pct.    Lawson said that under the government's program of sellingoff state industries to the private sector the number of share-holders in the country had trebled since 1979 and nowrepresented one in five of the adult population. REUTER&#3;